"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532999","Wales Office","false","2016-07-11","<p>The Government has made no assessment of the proportion of legislation currently in force that applies to Wales only.</p><p>The quantum of law made by the National Assembly for Wales is, and will remain, small compared to the body of law that is common to England and Wales.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2016-07-11T11:56:57.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532999/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532999/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532999/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-07-05","Legislation: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what proportion of legislation currently in force applies to Wales only.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","41954"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533000","Wales Office","true","2016-07-13","<p><del class="ministerial">The Prime Minister has been clear that the negotiation for Britain's future relationship with Europe will need to begin under a new Prime Minister, and we have now got to look at all the detailed arrangements. In the meantime, Departments continue working to deliver the Government agenda</del></p><p><ins class="ministerial">The current EU funding rules will continue to apply until the UK has left the EU, following the successful conclusion of exit negotiations. It will be for the new Prime Minister and their Cabinet to discuss development funding in the future.</ins></p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2016-07-13T09:23:16.163Z","2016-07-13T10:19:45.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533000/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533000/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533000/answer","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533000/answer/previousversion/6838","Biography information for Alun Cairns","28","Wales","Wales","2016-07-05","EU Grants and Loans: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what plans he has to ensure that the Government commits to providing  the same level of funding to Wales after the UK leaves the EU that is received from the EU.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","41923"
