"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533045","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-07-08","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring that the UK remains open for business and continues to grow and thrive. Ensuring our new relationship with the EU works for employees and employers will be important in the months ahead</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-07-08T12:33:31.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533045/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533045/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533045/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-07-05","USA: Climate Change Convention","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of reports that non-UK EU companies are reconsidering or withdrawing job offers to UK nationals, what assessment they have made of whether prospective employees will have access to a more limited pool of opportunities.","false","Biography information for Lord Cromwell",,"Lord Cromwell","HL1008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533046","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-07-13","<p>As my Rt hon Friend the Prime Minister has said, there will be no immediate changes as a result of the EU referendum, including in the circumstances of non-UK EU citizens working in the UK. The Government is committed to ensuring that the UK remains open for business and continues to grow and thrive. Ensuring our new relationship with the EU works for employees and employers will be important in the months ahead.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-07-13T14:13:17.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533046/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533046/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533046/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-07-05","United Arab Emirates: Qatar","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of reports that non-UK EU citizens are reconsidering job offers from UK companies, what assessment they have made of whether prospective employers in the UK will have access to a more limited pool of skills.","false","Biography information for Lord Cromwell",,"Lord Cromwell","HL1009"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533047","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-07-15","<p>The main streams of funds available to UK universities and research bodies are Horizon 2020, Erasmus Plus and aspects of the European Structural and Investment Funds.</p><p>Under Horizon 2020, the current Framework Programme, the UK has been awarded €1.84bn to date[1] (excluding the Euratom nuclear research and training programme).</p><p>In 2014, the first year of the Erasmus Plus Programme, the UK obtained €79.08 million for mobility grants to 36,734 people from all educational sectors to study, train and volunteer abroad. A further €30.66m was obtained for cooperation projects<sup>[2]</sup>.</p><p>The UK’s strategy<sup>[3]</sup> for its 2014-2020 allocations from the European Structural and Investment Funds sets out that €1.6bn was earmarked for the theme of research, technological development and innovation.</p><p>As the Prime Minister has made clear, while the UK remains a member of the EU, current EU funding arrangements continue unchanged, including those that apply to students, researchers, and businesses. It will be for the Government under the new Prime Minister to begin the negotiation to leave, and set out arrangements for those currently in receipt of EU funds.</p><p> </p><p>The UK economy is fundamentally strong and our research and innovation are world leading. The Government intends to maintain and enhance the strength of our research base.</p><p> </p><ol><li><p>UK participation in H2020 and FP7, BIS occasional (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/uk-participation-in-horizon-2020-and-framework-programme-7" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/uk-participation-in-horizon-2020-and-framework-programme-7</a>)</p></li><li><p>Ref: <a href="https://www.britishcouncil.org/organisation/press/british-council-ecorys-uk-delighted-win-erasmus" target="_blank">https://www.britishcouncil.org/organisation/press/british-council-ecorys-uk-delighted-win-erasmus</a>.</p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368808/bis-14-1179-united-kingdom-partnership-agreement-part-one.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368808/bis-14-1179-united-kingdom-partnership-agreement-part-one.pdf</a></p></li></ol><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-07-15T10:12:45.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533047/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533047/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533047/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-07-05","Crimes of Violence: Young People","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much EU funding is currently accessible by UK universities and research bodies; and what assessment they have made of the impact of the referendum on the UK’s membership of the EU on (1) such funding in the future, and (2) UK universities’ and research bodies’ ability to develop and sustain world-class research and educational programmes.","false","Biography information for Lord Cromwell",,"Lord Cromwell","HL1010"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533048","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-14","The UK never publicises how it votes in these matters. Saudi Arabia did not need our support in the last election to the Human Rights Council since they were uncontested.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-14T14:58:58.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533048/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533048/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533048/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-05","Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to support the re-election of Saudi Arabia to the UN Human Rights Council for a second term.","false","Biography information for Baroness Deech",,"Baroness Deech","HL1011"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533049","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-14","<p>The International Monetary Fund Board meeting in May 2016 noted Zimbabwe’s good progress and encouraged further reform. Whilst this Government welcomes Zimbabwe’s progress, full re-engagement will only be possible once the Zimbabwean government has demonstrated a clear commitment to economic and political reform.</p><p> </p><p>British Ministers and officials have met Chinamasa in recent months, including the Parliamentary Under Secretary of State at the Department for International Development, my Hon Friend the Member for Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner (Nick Hurd), in May and the Minister for Africa, my Hon Friend the Member for Rochford and Southend East (James Duddridge), in July. In these meetings, Ministers emphasised to Chinamasa the importance of urgent economic and political reforms in Zimbabwe if there is to be further progress on re-engagement with the International Financial Institutions.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-14T14:59:45.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533049/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533049/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533049/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-05","India: China","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the likelihood that the government of Zimbabwe will comply with the obligations required for re-entry to the global financial system.","false","Biography information for Lord Oates",,"Lord Oates","HL1012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533050","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-22","<p>Zimbabwe’s re-engagement with the International Financial Institutions will only be possible once it has demonstrated a clear commitment to economic and political reform. We, along with the wider international community, have made this clear to the Zimbabwean government.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-22T10:23:13.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533050/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533050/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533050/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-05","A130","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the government of Zimbabwe's previous breaches of domestic and international commitments, what assessment they have made of the risk of it breaching the commitments required for re-entry to the global financial system.","false","Biography information for Lord Oates",,"Lord Oates","HL1013"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533051","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","true","2016-07-14","<p>British Ministers and officials have met <ins class="ministerial">Zimbabwe’s Finance Minister Patrick </ins>Chinamasa in recent months, including the Parliamentary Under Secretary of State at the Department for International Development, my Hon Friend the Member for Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner (Nick Hurd), in May and the Minister for Africa, my Hon Friend the Member for Rochford and Southend East (James Duddridge), in July. In these meetings, Ministers emphasised to <ins class="ministerial">Minister </ins>Chinamasa the importance of urgent economic and political reforms in Zimbabwe if there is to be further progress on re-engagement with the International Financial Institutions.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-14T14:58:05.62Z","2016-07-22T13:04:35.787Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533051/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533051/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533051/answer",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533051/answer/previousversion/6889","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-05","British Nationality","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether ministers plan to meet Zimbabwe's Finance Minister Patrick Chinamasa prior to the decision of the International Monetary Fund on whether Zimbabwe should be re-admitted to the global financial system.","false","Biography information for Lord Oates",,"Lord Oates","HL1014"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533052","HM Treasury","false","2016-07-15","<p>I refer the noble Lord to the most recent statutory report which the Treasury provided to Parliament as required by Section 2 of the Loans to Ireland Act 2010. The last report was laid in Parliament on 26 April 2016 and is available in the Printed Paper Office.</p><p>The timetable for repayment set out in this report remains unchanged.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2016-07-15T10:13:36.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533052/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533052/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533052/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-07-05","Offenders: Deportation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the outcome of the referendum on the UK's membership of the EU, when the Irish Republic will repay the funding it received from the UK as a result of the 2008 financial crisis, and how much is still owed.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL1015"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533053","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-07-21","<p>The people of the United Kingdom have voted to leave the European Union and their will must be respected and delivered. The interests of all parts of our United Kingdom must be protected and advanced. As we prepare for a new negotiation with the European Union, we will fully involve the Scottish, Welsh and Northern Ireland governments.</p><p> </p><p>The Government remains fully committed to the Belfast Agreement, its fundamental principles, and its successors and to the institutions they establish.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Dunlop",,"2016-07-21T14:08:13.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533053/answer","Biography information for Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533053/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533053/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-07-05","Muslim Brotherhood Review","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the concept of parity of esteem, as outlined in the Belfast Agreement 1998, will be involved in any way in the arrangements for withdrawal from the EU, and if so, how.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL1016"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533054","Department of Health","false","2016-07-12","<p>The Department has not made a formal assessment of the effect of the decision to abolish the Nursing, Midwifery and Allied Health Professionals policy unit on the roles of Professional Adviser for Allied Health Professions and Professional Adviser for Mental Health, Learning Disability and Dementia Care.</p><p> </p><p>As part of the DH 2020 plan, the Department is changing the way it works to deliver its essential work for the Government while achieving efficiency savings. The Department’s approach is to flexibly access professional advice from a wide range of sources, including arms-length bodies, regulators, stakeholders and professional bodies, rather than from a fixed standing team of internal advisers.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-07-12T15:25:18.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533054/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533054/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533054/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-05","British Nationality: English Language","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the effect of the decision to abolish the Nursing Midwifery and Allied Health Professionals policy unit within the Department of Health on the roles of Professional Adviser for Allied Health Professions and Professional Adviser for Mental Health, Learning Disability and Dementia Care.","false","Biography information for Lord Balfe",,"Lord Balfe","HL1017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533055","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-22","<p>We will make a decision on the ratification of the Economic Partnership Agreement (EPA) between the Southern African Development Community (SADC) and the European Union at a later date, in accordance with the best interests of the UK. We remain full members of the EU for now, and while the UK is still a member of the EU all existing rights and obligations will continue to apply. The Agreement will provisionally apply to the UK once it has been ratified by the European Parliament and SADC member states, irrespective of any UK ratification.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-22T10:24:04.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533055/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533055/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533055/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-05","Nuclear Weapons: Verification","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to ratify the Economic Partnership Agreement between the Southern African Development Community and the EU signed on 10 June.","false","Biography information for Lord Boateng",,"Lord Boateng","HL1018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533056","Cabinet Office","false","2016-07-20","<p>The process for leaving the EU and determining our future relationship will be a complex one, so we need to take time to think through our objectives and approach. We want to ensure the best possible outcome for Britain and the future UK-EU relationship. The Prime Minister has also said we would not trigger Article 50 until we have a UK approach and objectives.</p>",,"Baroness Chisholm of Owlpen",,"2016-07-20T10:51:05.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533056/answer","Biography information for Baroness Chisholm of Owlpen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533056/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533056/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-07-05","Nuclear Disarmament: Conferences","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they intend to publish an impact assessment before invoking Article 50 of the Treaty on European Union.","false","Biography information for Lord Hutton of Furness",,"Lord Hutton of Furness","HL1019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533886","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-07-11","<p>The Prime Minister has been clear that the negotiation for Britain's future relationship with Europe will need to begin under a new Prime Minister, and we have now got to look at all the detailed arrangements. In the meantime, Departments continue working to deliver the Government agenda.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-07-11T14:54:57.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533886/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533886/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/533886/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-07-05","Department for Work and Pensions: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the potential policy implications for his Department of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for John Nicolson","East Dunbartonshire","John  Nicolson","905756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/534971","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-07-11","<p>This government is committed to halving the disability employment gap. In the spending review we announced a real terms spending increase on supporting disabled people into work.</p><p> </p><p>In the last two years, 365,000 disabled people have entered employment. Our forthcoming Green Paper will set out our plans to support more disabled people into work.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-07-11T15:19:14.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/534971/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/534971/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/534971/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-07-05","Employment: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to support people with disabilities and health conditions who are looking for work.","false","Biography information for Glyn Davies","Montgomeryshire","Glyn Davies","905772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535664","Wales Office","false","2016-07-13","<p>Wales’s inward investment performance show we can thrive on the world stage. Last year’s UKTI figures showed a record level of inward investment, with over 100 FDI projects supporting over 5,000 jobs. More recent indicators suggest Wales is on course for another great year.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2016-07-13T16:33:58.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535664/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535664/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535664/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-07-05","Foreign Investment in UK: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what assessment he has made of trends in the level of inward investment in Wales.","false","Biography information for Steve Double","St Austell and Newquay","Steve Double","905793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535665","Wales Office","false","2016-07-13","<p>I visited Coleg Cambria last week to attend the North Wales Growth Deal Summit with the Welsh Government Cabinet Secretary Ken Skates, the North Wales Economic Ambition Board, Mersey Dee Alliance, the Rail Task Force, CBI and the FSB.</p><p> </p><p>It is vital that partners come together to bring forward a deal that works across the border and drives economic growth.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2016-07-13T16:34:38.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535665/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535665/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-07-05","Local Growth Deals: North Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what recent progress the Government has made on a North Wales growth deal.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","905792"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535666","Wales Office","false","2016-07-13","<p>I am proud to champion Wales on the international stage. I will be meeting the Minister for Trade and Investment tomorrow to discuss strengthening Wales’ international business links, and have committed to a roundtable discussion with businesses and UKTI in the autumn – the first of many such meetings.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2016-07-13T16:32:53.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535666/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535666/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535666/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-07-05","Overseas Trade: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, if he will take steps to strengthen Wales' international business links.","false","Biography information for Mr William Wragg","Hazel Grove","William Wragg","905797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535667","Wales Office","false","2016-07-13","<p>This Government has underwritten Welsh Government borrowing powers of up to £500 million to help deliver vital improvements to Welsh infrastructure, particularly the M4. Upgrading the route has been identified by businesses and commuters as a priority for decades. It is time for work to begin.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns","905791","2016-07-13T16:36:18.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535667/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535667/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535667/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-07-05","Motorways: Newport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what recent assessment he has made of the potential effect on the economy in Wales of upgrading the M4 relief road.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","905796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535668","Wales Office","false","2016-07-13","<p>This Government has underwritten Welsh Government borrowing powers of up to £500 million to help deliver vital improvements to Welsh infrastructure, particularly the M4. Upgrading the route has been identified by businesses and commuters as a priority for decades. It is time for work to begin.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns","905796","2016-07-13T16:36:18.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535668/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535668/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535668/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-07-05","Motorways: Newport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what recent assessment he has made of the potential effect on the economy in Wales of upgrading the M4 relief road.","false","Biography information for Luke Hall","Thornbury and Yate","Luke Hall","905791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532322","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-13","<p>Freedom of religion or belief in Sudan continues to be an area of deep concern to the British Government. Along with international partners, we regularly attend court cases on freedom of religion or belief and raise related cases with the Government of Sudan. Through our project work we also seek to support lawyers who take on cases addressing important human rights issues, such as freedom of religion. More broadly, we also continue highlight our concerns about the conflict in South Kordofan, most recently via a joint statement with our Troika partners on 27 May. We welcome the Government of Sudan’s announcement of a cessation of hostilities on 17 June and urge all sides to respect this.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-13T15:18:03.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532322/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532322/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532322/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Public Sector: Equality","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of continued reports of the imprisonment of Christians, increased restrictions on refugee churches, closure and destruction of other churches, and the ongoing bombing campaign against the Nuba region which has a large Christian community, what steps they are taking to ensure that the right to freedom of religion or belief is respected in Sudan.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532323","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-14","The UK remains a member of the EU until the process of leaving is concluded. Consequently, rights and obligations in the EU Treaties and other EU law continue to apply until that time.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-14T15:51:34.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532323/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532323/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532323/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Small Businesses: Bank Services","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether ministers and civil servants are required to comply with and execute EU law, and under what circumstances they can depart from the requirements of EU law prior to the date when withdrawal from the EU triggered by Article 50 is completed.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532324","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-07-12","<p>The decision that the Red Arrows would not perform at Fowey Royal Regatta this year was made by the Fowey Royal Regatta Committee.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-07-12T15:23:27.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532324/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532324/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532324/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-07-04","5G","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what are the safety reasons behind the Red Arrows' decision not to perform at Fowey Royal Regatta this year.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532325","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-12","<p>Dobwalls Bypass opened to traffic in December 2008 and included the construction of two purpose built bat bridges: Havett Farm Bridge and Lantoom Quarry Bridge. Sample monitoring of the effectiveness of the bridges has been undertaken. The surveys recorded 23 bat crossings over two days in June 2008, compared to a total of 39 bat crossings over two days in July 2014. The results of the surveys are not directly comparable as they were conducted in different months and at different times of day.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-07-12T10:58:00.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532325/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532325/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532325/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-07-04","Broadband","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many bats are currently estimated to be using the bat bridges built over the Dobwalls bypass in Cornwall; and how that number compares with the number recorded at the opening of the bridges.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532326","Department for Education","false","2016-07-26","<p>As a matter of principle all children resident in the UK are entitled to receive a free state-school education. We want to reassure European citizens living in the UK that there will be no immediate changes in their circumstances.</p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2016-07-26T15:44:40.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532326/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532326/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532326/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-07-04","Mayors: Elections","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the referendum on the UK membership of the EU, whether school children from other EU countries enrolled in British schools will be able to complete their education in the UK without interruption.","false","Biography information for Baroness Goudie",,"Baroness Goudie","HL923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532327","Home Office","false","2016-07-14","<p>The Government wants to be able to guarantee the legal status of EU nationals who are living in the UK, and we are confident that we will be able to do this.</p><p>But we must also win the same rights for British nationals living in European countries, and it will be an early negotiating objective for the Government to achieve those things together.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-07-14T13:02:54.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532327/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532327/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532327/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-07-04","Times of Sittings","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the referendum of the UK membership of the EU, whether families and individuals already established in the UK, including families and individuals from other EU countries, will be able to stay in the UK whatever changes may be made in regard to future migration to the UK.","false","Biography information for Baroness Goudie",,"Baroness Goudie","HL924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532328","Home Office","false","2016-07-14","<p>According to the UNHCR’s online list of participating States Hungary acceded to the 1951 Convention and 1967 Protocol on 14 March 1989.</p><p>The EU Procedures Directive sets out when a Member State may declare an asylum claim inadmissible, including when it is permissible to return an asylum applicant to a safe third country. Hungary is also bound by the EU Returns Directive, which includes safeguards for individuals facing removal from participating States.</p><p>Member States' implementation and compliance with EU legislation is a matter for the European Commission and the European Court of Justice. The Government has no plans to make representations to the Government of Hungary on this issue.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-07-14T13:03:35.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532328/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532328/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532328/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-07-04","Business: Regulation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether Hungary has ratified the UN Convention on Refugees; and whether they will make representations to the government of Hungary about not expelling any applicants for asylum before their cases have been examined and decided.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532329","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-15","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) was allocated £422.9 million of Official Development Assistance funds to spend in Financial Year 2015-2016. When finalised, the figures will be published on the FCO website and registered on the UK data portal and on the International Aid Transparency Initiative portal.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-15T13:42:44.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532329/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532329/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532329/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Fire Regulations","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much the Foreign and Commonwealth Office spent on Overseas Development Assistance between April 2015 and March 2016, and what measures were used to ensure high levels of transparency in how that money was spent.","false","Biography information for Baroness Northover",,"Baroness Northover","HL926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532330","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-07-12","<p>The Department for International Development (DFID) is responsible for publishing the UK's Overseas Development Assistance (ODA) figures for the previous calendar year in their annual National Statistics publications. Provisional figures for ODA expenditure by the Ministry of Defence (MOD) in 2016 will be published by DFID no later than April 2017. In 2015, the MOD provisionally spent £9.2 million on ODA-eligible activities. Final figures for 2015 will be published in 'Statistics on International Development' on www.gov.uk in autumn 2016. This publication will include detailed project-level data to comply with transparency initiatives.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-07-12T15:22:58.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532330/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532330/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532330/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-07-04","Impact Assessments","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much the Ministry of Defence spent on Overseas Development Assistance between April 2015 and March 2016, and what measures were used to ensure high levels of transparency in how that money was spent.","false","Biography information for Baroness Northover",,"Baroness Northover","HL927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532331","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-14","<p>The UK strongly welcomes the plan agreed between the EU and Turkey to end irregular migration from Turkey to the EU. For the first time, we have a plan that breaks the business model of the people smugglers by cutting the link between getting in a boat and getting settlement in Europe. The numbers of migrants arriving on Greek islands has significantly reduced since this deal came into effect and it is making a genuine difference to managing the flows of migration; preventing people from dying in attempting the crossing or putting themselves in the hands of smugglers.</p><p>The UK takes the view that Turkey offers sufficient protection, in its law and its practice, to return people there. Turkey is already hosting over 2.7 million Syrian refugees and has granted them access to healthcare, education and the labour market. We are also pleased to note that, since the 18 March EU-Turkey migration deal, Turkey has reached agreements with the European Commission and the UN High Commissioner for Refugees in providing them with access to the Düziçi Camp and Kirklareli Removal Centre. The UK continues to work with Turkey to deliver further improvements to their immigration and asylum services.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-14T14:38:39.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532331/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532331/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532331/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Regulation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the EU's refugee deal with Turkey, what impact assessment has been made of the impact of that deal on the safety and security of Syrian refugees.","false","Biography information for Lord Roberts of Llandudno",,"Lord Roberts of Llandudno","HL928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532332","Home Office","false","2016-07-12","<p>In answer to Question HL929, I refer the noble Lord to my answer on 28 June 2016 for Question HL718. In answer to Questions HL930, I refer the noble Lord to my answer on 27 June 2016 for Question HL719.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","HL930","2016-07-12T16:34:52.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532332/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532332/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532332/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-07-04","Bahrain: Life Imprisonment","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what percentage of asylum applications have been accepted in the UK in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Lord Roberts of Llandudno",,"Lord Roberts of Llandudno","HL929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532333","Home Office","false","2016-07-12","<p>In answer to Question HL929, I refer the noble Lord to my answer on 28 June 2016 for Question HL718. In answer to Questions HL930, I refer the noble Lord to my answer on 27 June 2016 for Question HL719.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","HL929","2016-07-12T16:34:52.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532333/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532333/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532333/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-07-04","Bahrain: Protest","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what percentage of asylum applications to the UK in the last 12 months were from Syrian minors, and what percentage of those applications were accepted.","false","Biography information for Lord Roberts of Llandudno",,"Lord Roberts of Llandudno","HL930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532334","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-07-11","<p>There are no current contractual obligations for Personal Independence Payment assessment providers (Atos and Capita) to provide an audio-recording of consultations. Claimants may use their own equipment to record their face-to-face consultation should they wish, subject to any reasonable conditions the Department place on such recordings.</p><p>We regularly keep our position on recording under review and will be having further dialogue with the Assessment Providers on this point.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Altmann",,"2016-07-11T14:26:36.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532334/answer","Biography information for Baroness Altmann","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532334/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532334/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-07-04","Bahrain: Technical Assistance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with Atos and Capita about introducing audio recordings of Personal Independence Payment assessments.","false","Biography information for Baroness Thomas of Winchester",,"Baroness Thomas of Winchester","HL931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532335","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-07-11","<p>The Department is committed to ensuring that all Personal Independence Payment (PIP) claimants receive high quality, objective, fair and accurate assessments. The Department closely monitors all aspects of the process including the performance of the assessment providers, Atos Healthcare and Capita.</p><p>From 1<sup>st</sup> July 2016, we implemented an independent audit of PIP throughout Great Britain. This covers an audit of assessments carried out by our providers to ensure that the advice they provide to the Department's decision makers is of suitable quality, is fully explained and is justified.</p>",,"Baroness Altmann",,"2016-07-11T13:47:20.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532335/answer","Biography information for Baroness Altmann","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532335/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532335/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-07-04","Sayed Alwadaei","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how they monitor Personal Independence Payment assessments for accuracy.","false","Biography information for Baroness Thomas of Winchester",,"Baroness Thomas of Winchester","HL932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532336","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-07-11","<p>Health Professionals must support their evaluation of the claimant’s health condition by an examination of all submitted materials thereby ensuring that the information provided to the Department’s Decision Makers is fully explained and justified.</p><p>The Department closely monitors all aspects of the process including the performance of Health Professionals to ensure that the advice they provide to the Department's Decision Makers is of suitable quality.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Altmann",,"2016-07-11T14:26:12.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532336/answer","Biography information for Baroness Altmann","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532336/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532336/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-07-04","Al-Sayed Alawi Hussain al-Alawi,","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how they ensure that all medical reports presented by claimants at Personal Independence Payment assessments are read by assessors.","false","Biography information for Baroness Thomas of Winchester",,"Baroness Thomas of Winchester","HL933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532337","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-07-11","<p>All Personal Independence Payment (PIP) assessment sites must be fully compliant with the Equality Act 2010 with suitable ground floor accommodation available. The assessment providers are required to ensure that the needs of all PIP claimants are considered, including proximity to public transport routes and access to suitable parking.</p><p>Before attending a face-to-face consultation, claimants are informed that they can alert their assessment provider of any additional requirements that they may have and the providers will meet any such reasonable requests.<strong> </strong></p><p>Where appropriate, assessments may also be carried out in a claimant’s home.</p>",,"Baroness Altmann",,"2016-07-11T13:58:41.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532337/answer","Biography information for Baroness Altmann","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532337/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532337/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-07-04","Teachers: Training","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether all Personal Independence Payment assessment centres are accessible for disabled people.","false","Biography information for Baroness Thomas of Winchester",,"Baroness Thomas of Winchester","HL934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532338","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-13","We have not raised this issue with the Israeli authorities. We previously welcomed the easing of fishing restrictions, and continue to encourage the Israeli authorities to implement further measures to improve the situation on the ground in Gaza. The UK would like to see a permanent increase in the size of the fishing zone off the coast of Gaza, in line with the limit of twenty nautical miles stipulated in the Oslo accords.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-13T15:11:21.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532338/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532338/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532338/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Sixth Form Colleges: Finance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel regarding the reduction of the permitted fishing zone off the coast of the Gaza Strip from nine to six nautical miles.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532339","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-13","Our officials in Tel Aviv have not raised this specific issue of the use of sponge-tipped bullets with the Israeli authorities. We do, however, raise our concerns with them about the manner in which the Israel Defence Forces police non-violent protests, including the use of lethal and non-lethal ammunition.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-13T15:12:08.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532339/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532339/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532339/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Supply Teachers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action they plan to take regarding the reported use of sponge-tipped bullets against Palestinians by Israeli forces.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532340","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-13","<p>We have not made any representations to the Israeli authorities on this issue. However, our Embassy in Tel Aviv regularly raises concern over the excessive use of force with the Israeli authorities including the use of non-lethal ammunition during non-violent protests.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-13T15:12:25.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532340/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532340/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532340/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Brexit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel following reports of the use of rubber bullets and gas canisters, and the confiscation of vehicles, by the Israeli Defence Forces during a raid on Bil'in village on 16 June.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532341","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-13","<p>Whilst we have not made any assessment of the non-violent protests by the village of Bil’in, officials from our Consulate General in Jerusalem met Abdullah Abu Rahmah (coordinator of Bil’in Popular Struggle Committee) in his capacity as Deputy Head of the Palestinian Authority Commission against the Wall and Settlements in 20 August 2015. The Consulate General worked with the Commission on a joint olive harvest campaign, and are looking to provide similar support to Palestinian communities in the future.</p><p>Abu Rahmeh has been arrested by the Israel Defence Forces multiple times for taking part in non violent resistance and has been designated a human rights defender by the EU. UK officials attended his court hearing on 8 February 2015, with representatives from other EU Missions.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-13T15:13:08.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532341/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532341/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532341/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Food Supply","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the weekly non-violent protests against illegal Israeli settlements by the village of Bil'in, and whether they plan to hold discussions with that village's Popular Struggle Committee.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532342","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-14","<p>We have not made any representations to the Israeli authorities on this issue.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-14T15:51:45.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532342/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532342/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532342/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Gaza: Utilities","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel regarding the reported closure of Palestinian media outlet Musawa for a second time in a year.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL939"
