"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532465","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-07-07","<p>There have been a number of challenges with the introduction of the Basic Payment Scheme in its first year. These include the implementation of a new IT solution; new European Commission requirements of the scheme such as greening and the associated administrative checks and the move to the use of established pre-populated forms and processes for 2015.</p><p>As of 3 July 86,760 (99.6%) of farmers have received a payment on their 2015 BPS claim. The Rural Payments Agency continues to focus on making top up payments to those farmers who have already received a bridging payment.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-07-07T16:25:58.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532465/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532465/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532465/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-07-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the main reasons for delays in basic farm payments were in the most recent year for which information is available; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","41745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532466","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-07-12","<p>Defra does not pay any additional incentives to staff for working overtime on top of the normal departmental overtime payments.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-07-12T12:34:29.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532466/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532466/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532466/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-07-04","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, (a) how much has been paid to officials of her Department as an additional incentive for working overtime on top of their normal overtime payments, (b) how much has been offered to any individual staff member for a one-off occurrence, (c) how many staff received such incentivised additional payments, (d) from which budgets such payments were made and (e) at which Ministerial or official level the business cases or payment approval for such payments was made in (i) each of the last five years and (ii) 2016 to date.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","41807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532467","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-07-12","<p>Bee Health is a devolved matter. The decision to join BeeBase is a matter for each devolved government to make in conjunction with Defra.</p><p> </p><p>Beekeepers in Northern Ireland can benefit from the wealth of information on the public pages of BeeBase which provide advice and guidance on identification of bee pests and diseases and good beekeeping practices to keep their hives healthy.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-07-12T12:37:49.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532467/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532467/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532467/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-07-04","Bees: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, for what reasons Northern Irish beekeepers are prevented from registering on BeeBase.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","41796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532468","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-07-12","<p>Bee health is a devolved matter. In England, Defra supports beekeepers through the work of the National Bee Unit (NBU). NBU Bee Inspectors carry out inspections of over 5,000 apiaries each year looking for bee pests and diseases. Where key pests and diseases are found the inspectors take necessary statutory action for their control. They also provide beekeepers with free training and advice.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-07-12T12:33:30.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532468/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532468/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532468/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-07-04","Bees: Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to support beekeepers whose colonies are at risk from fatal diseases.","false","Biography information for Tom Elliott","Fermanagh and South Tyrone","Tom Elliott","41793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532469","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-07-07","<p>Natural England collects data relating to sightings or signs of exotic mammals including big cats. Data on sightings of big cats, reported to Natural England and its predecessors between 2000 and 2012, can be found by accessing the Natural England section of the National Archives website.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Data for big cat sightings from 2013 is as follows.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>No. cases reported</p></td><td><p>No. individual animals reported</p></td><td><p>Confirmed</p></td><td><p>Supported but not confirmed</p></td><td><p>Discounted</p></td><td><p>Probably other cause</p></td><td><p>Inconclusive</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>There have been no big cat sightings so far this year.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-07-07T12:23:53.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532469/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532469/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532469/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-07-04","Cats","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many big cat sightings have been reported in each year from (a) 2000 to 2010, (b) 2015 and (c) 2016 to date.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","41777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532470","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-07-07","<p>The Government will release single-use carrier bag data on or before 31 July this year for the reporting period 5 October 2015 – 6 April 2016. The release will include a summary of the significant points, incorporating an indication of the reduction in single-use carrier bag usage.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-07-07T12:14:35.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532470/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532470/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-07-04","Plastic Bags","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether her Department plans to produce data on the reduction in single-use plastic carrier bag usage in England for the period ending 6 April 2016.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","41748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532471","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-07-07","<p>A ban on the use of wild animals in travelling circuses is a manifesto commitment and will be introduced as soon as parliamentary time allows. In the interim, the welfare of any wild animals still being used by travelling circuses in England is protected by the Welfare of Wild Animals in Travelling Circuses (England) Regulations 2012. Currently, 17 wild animals are licensed by Defra under the Regulations for use by two circuses.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-07-07T11:27:56.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532471/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532471/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532471/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-07-04","Animal Welfare: Circuses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the Government's policy is on banning wild animals from being used in circuses.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","41749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532472","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-07","<p>We are concerned about the recent extension of the imprisonment of Al Wefaq’s Secretary-General, Sheikh Ali Salman. We continue to raise his case with the Government of Bahrain. I did so most recently on 2 June when I met with the Bahraini Undersecretary for Foreign Affairs at the biannual UK-Bahrain Joint Working Group meeting, and the Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond) did so most recently with his Bahraini counterpart, Sheikh Khalid Bin Ahmad Al Khalifa on 14 June 2016.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-07-07T13:52:59.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532472/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532472/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Bahrain: Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what his policy is on the extension of the prison sentence from four years to nine years of Sheikh Ali Salman in Bahrain; and what representations he has made to the government of Bahrain on that extension.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","41724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532473","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-07","<p>We continue to follow this case closely, raising it at Ministerial and Official level at every opportunity, as we have done since November 2013. The case has now been raised at Ministerial level 38 times since November 2013. The Prime Minister, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron) raised it for the fifth time in a letter to Prime Minister Modi in June. I raised the case in April with the Foreign Secretary of India while he was in London and most recently in May during my visit to India when accompanied by the British High Commissioner I also visited the men in prison. While we cannot interfere in the Indian legal process, we will continue to use every opportunity to raise the case at all levels.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-07-07T13:57:00.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532473/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532473/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","India: Shipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what progress has been made on efforts to free the Seamen Guard Ohio crew.","false","Biography information for Gavin Robinson","Belfast East","Gavin Robinson","41797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532474","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-12","It is the policy of the UK Government that recognition of genocide is a matter for judicial decision, rather than for governments or non-judicial bodies. While the terrible suffering cannot be forgotten and we must continue to remember and honour the victims of the past, we believe the UK’s priority today should be to promote reconciliation between the peoples and Governments of Turkey and Armenia and to find a way for these two countries to face their joint history together.","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-07-12T16:18:33.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532474/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532474/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532474/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Armenia: Genocide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Government plans to recognise the mass killings of Armenian Christians by the Ottoman Empire as genocide.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","41788"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532475","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-12","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office does not make any additional incentive payments over and above overtime payments to which staff may be entitled.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-07-12T16:39:32.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532475/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532475/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, (a) how much has been paid to officials of his Department as an additional incentive for working overtime on top of their normal overtime payments, (b) how much has been offered to any individual staff member for a one-off occurrence, (c) how many staff received such incentivised additional payments, (d) from which budgets such payments were made and (e) at which Ministerial or official level the business cases or payment approval for such payments was made in (i) each of the last five years and (ii) 2016 to date.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","41808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532476","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-11","The recent increase in inter-faith tensions in Burma, the incidents in Bago and Hpakant and anti-Muslim protests in Rakhine State, are extremely concerning. I understand that arrests have been made following the burning of the Muslim prayer hall in Hpakant. I call on the Burmese Government to do everything within its power to tackle hate speech and ensure freedom of religion or belief and rule of law for all Burma’s communities. Our Embassy in Rangoon is continuing to monitor the situation closely.","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-07-11T15:37:25.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532476/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532476/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Burma: Religious Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to encourage the government of Burma to establish an independent investigation into the destruction of buildings in a mosque compound in the Bago Region in central Burma.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","41817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532477","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-08","<p>We are aware of reports of the alleged use of UK –supplied cluster munitions by Saudi Arabia in the Yemen. The Government takes such allegations very seriously. We are analysing the case and seeking clarification from the Saudi-led Coalition.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-07-08T12:37:29.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532477/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532477/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Yemen: Cluster Munitions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what information his Department holds on steps taken by the government of Saudi Arabia to investigate the possible use of UK-supplied BL-755 cluster munitions in northern Yemen.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","41818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532478","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-11","The Foreign Secretary, my Right Hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond) last discussed these cases with Foreign Minister Zarif on 4 July. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office’s Director of Consular Services raised all of the detained UK-Iranian dual nationals with the Iranian Chargé d’affaires on 29 June, as did I, with the Iranian Chargé on 18 May. The British Embassy in Tehran continues to raise all our consular cases with the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, most recently on 4 July. Iran does not recognise dual nationality of Iranian citizens which prevents information being provided to us about their detention.","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-07-11T15:11:21.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532478/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532478/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532478/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Iran: Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations his Department has made to the government of Iran on the cases of (a) Kamal Foroughi and (b) Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","41820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532479","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-12","<p>Any legal representations would be for Mr Foroughi’s legal team to consider and pursue within Iran. The Iranian Ministry of Foreign Affairs has told the British Embassy in Tehran that Mr Foroughi’s lawyers would be welcome to have contact with the Iranian Judicial authorities.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-07-12T16:28:25.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532479/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532479/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Iran: Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will urge the government of Iran to apply without discrimination Article 58 of the Islamic Penal Code to permit Kamal Foroughi's early release.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","41821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532480","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-11","<p>Female Genital Mutilation is unacceptable and we are committed to working to eradicate this horrific practice.</p><p>Nigeria is one of 17 countries targeted by the Department for International Development’s £35 million programme working towards ending Female Genital Mutilation/Cutting in Africa.</p><p>The programme focuses on three areas: building the evidence base for tackling Female Genital Mutilation, working with the UN on challenging social norms and with governments on policy measures, as well as support for Africa-led campaigns.</p><p>Our broader development programme in Nigeria also includes initiatives that tackle violence against women and girls. This includes UK support for implementation of the Violence Against Persons (Prohibition) Act, which criminalises female genital mutilation.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-07-11T14:38:58.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532480/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532480/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Nigeria: Female Genital Mutilation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent steps his Department has taken to prevent or reduce the incidence of female genital mutilation in Nigeria.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","41822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532481","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-12","<p>The UK continues to recognise Turkey’s extraordinary generosity in hosting over three million refugees from Syria and elsewhere. Turkey now hosts more refugees than any other country in the world, and offers refugees access to healthcare, labour and education.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-07-12T13:47:19.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532481/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532481/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Turkey: Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the level of support provided by the Turkish government to refugees and asylum seekers in that country.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","41819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532482","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-07","<p>I attended the French ministerial meeting on 3 June in Paris, where a joint communiqué was agreed. We remain in close contact with the French government about their plans for follow-up work and will make decisions about possible UK participation as further detail emerges.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-07-07T13:54:27.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532482/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532482/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532482/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether UK Ministers plan to participate in discussions initiated by the French government on the Middle East peace process.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","41741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532483","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-08","<p>The Ombudsman, Nawaf Mohammed Al Ma'awda, has issued a statement that addresses the full range of allegations and commits to undertake a full, independent investigation into the treatment of Mr Mohamed Ramadan. We appear not to have received any evidence in relation to this case.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-07-08T12:36:18.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532483/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532483/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532483/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Mohamed Ramadan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the Answer of 19 April 2016 to Question 33305, whether his Department had sight of the evidence submitted to the Ombudsman in Bahrain regarding Mr Mohamed Ramadan's case when preparing that Answer.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","41676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532484","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-07","The UK has been at the forefront of international efforts – in the EU, NATO, G7 and OSCE – to hold Russia to account for its aggression in Ukraine, and will continue to do so. The European Council, like the G7, has agreed that sanctions are linked to full implementation of the Minsk agreements. The Government will continue to push for this commitment to be upheld. EU economic sanctions against Russia were recently extended by unanimity for a further six months, until 31 January 2017.","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-07-07T16:34:55.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532484/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532484/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532484/answer","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532484/answer/previousversion/6212","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Russia: Sanctions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the UK leaving the EU on the (a) UK's and (b) EU's sanctions policy for Russia.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","41678"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532485","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-07-07","<p>The European Commission has recently taken the decision to propose the EU-Canada Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement (CETA) as a “mixed agreement” consisting of both EU and Member State competence. This means that CETA can only take full effect once the UK has decided to ratify it. As part of that ratification process, the complete draft text of the agreement would be laid before Parliament for 21 sitting days. In addition, the Government will ensure the proposals for a Council decision on signature, and subsequent conclusion, will be subject to scrutiny in both Houses of the UK Parliament.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-07-07T15:38:23.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532485/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532485/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532485/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-07-04","Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether the Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement will be considered an exclusive competence of the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","41750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532486","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-12","<p>The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), discussed Israel and the Occupied Palestinian Territories with French Foreign Minister Jean-Marc Ayrault on 7 June. During this meeting, they agreed to stay in close contact about the French government’s plans to follow up on their 3 June ministerial meeting. Foreign Office officials have since been in contact with their French counterparts.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-07-12T16:31:46.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532486/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532486/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532486/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-04","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions the Government has had with the French government on Israel and Palestine since the conference organised by the French government.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","41637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532487","Department of Health","false","2016-07-11","<p>The total cost to the National Health Service of drugs dispensed in England for the latest three years for which figures are available is shown in the table.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Primary care drugs spend <sup>1</sup></p></td><td><p>Secondary care drugs spend</p></td><td><p>Total drugs spend</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Outturn (£ million)</p></td><td><p>Outturn (£ million)</p></td><td><p>Outturn (£ million)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13 <sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>7,887</p></td><td><p>5,055</p></td><td><p>12,941</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14 <sup>3</sup></p></td><td><p>8,015</p></td><td><p>5,324</p></td><td><p>13,339</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>8,206</p></td><td><p>5,897</p></td><td><p>14,103</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Sources:</p><p><sup>1 </sup>Primary care figures to 2012/13 are from primary care trusts (PCTs) audited summarisation schedules. Figures from 2013/14 are from the Department’s annual report and accounts.</p><p><sup>2 </sup>Secondary care figures are from NHS trusts, PCT finance returns and foundation trust year-end accounts. Finance returns were not collected after 2011/12; figures for NHS trusts in 2012/13 are estimates.</p><p><sup>3</sup> Secondary care figures from 2013/14 are from Monitor and NHS Trust Development Authority.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-07-11T15:26:50.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532487/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532487/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532487/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-04","Prescription Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the market cost was of drugs provided through prescriptions in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","41651"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532488","Department of Health","false","2016-07-11","<p>The Government is committed to preventing and reducing the risk of harm to older adults in vulnerable situations regardless of the source of harm.</p><p> </p><p>The Care Act (2014) placed adult safeguarding on a statutory footing for the first time and provided local authorities with the lead on responding to, and preventing, abuse and neglect. Supported by a new duty of cooperation by other relevant agencies, set out in the Act, it has been made clear that safeguarding is everyone’s business. The statutory guidance to the Act sets out an expectation that local authorities ensure that the services they commission are safe, effective and of high quality. It also makes clear that those providing the service, local authorities and the Care Quality Commission take swift action where anyone alleges poor care, neglect or abuse.</p><p> </p><p>Behaviour which amounts to abuse and neglect often constitutes specific criminal offences. Although the local authority has the lead role in making enquiries, where criminal activity is suspected, then the early involvement of the police is likely to be appropriate in many cases, and that is what we would want to see.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-07-11T15:20:13.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532488/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532488/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532488/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-04","Older People: Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to tackle suspected abuse of the elderly by social carers.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","41647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532489","Department of Health","false","2016-07-07","<p>The proportion of National Health Service clinical staff who work part-time is in the attached table. The figures are taken from the Health and Social Care Information Centre’s monthly workforce statistics and cover staff working in NHS trusts and clinical commissioning groups.</p><p> </p><p>The number of NHS clinical staff who work part-time and are additionally registered as agency staff is not collected centrally.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","41738","2016-07-07T10:21:16.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532489/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532489/answer","PQ41738-PartTimeStaff-Table.xlsx","PQ41738-PartTimeStaff-Table.xlsx","Part-Time Staff Table","Part-Time Staff Table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532489/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-04","NHS: Part-time Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what proportion of NHS clinical staff that work part-time are additionally registered as agency staff.","false","Biography information for Graham Evans","Weaver Vale","Graham Evans","41739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532490","Department of Health","false","2016-07-12","<p>It is the responsibility of local National Health Service organisations to make decisions on the commissioning and funding of any healthcare treatments for NHS patients, taking account of issues to do with safety, clinical and cost-effectiveness and the availability of suitably qualified and regulated practitioners.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-07-12T12:56:08.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532490/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532490/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532490/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-04","Yoga","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of making yoga available through the NHS for treatment and recovery; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","41737"
