"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532492","Department of Health","false","2016-07-12","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) is currently appraising the peptide receptor radionuclide therapy treatment lutetium-177-DOTA octreotate for the treatment of neuroendocrine tumours and for gastroenteropancreatic neuroendocrine tumours.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that it will await the outcome of NICE’s appraisals before making any commissioning decisions on peptide receptor radionuclide therapy treatments.</p><p> </p><p>In the meantime, if a patient’s condition is considered clinically exceptional, then an application can be considered under NHS England’s Individual Funding Request system.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-07-12T10:26:12.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532492/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532492/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532492/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-04","Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to review the decision to remove peptide receptor radionuclide therapy treatments from the Cancer Drugs Fund list.","false","Biography information for David Tredinnick","Bosworth","David Tredinnick","41736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532493","Department of Health","false","2016-07-07","<p>Clinical commissioning groups are autonomous bodies which are responsible for managing spend as they deem appropriate. However, NHS England has published the guidance <em>Clinical Commissioning Groups: Remuneration guidance for Chief Officers (where the senior manager also undertakes the accountable officer role) and Chief Finance Officers </em>which can be found at this address:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Remuneration-guidance-final.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Remuneration-guidance-final.pdf</a></p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-07-07T08:31:03.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532493/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532493/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532493/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-04","Clinical Commissioning Groups: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the guidelines are for remuneration of chairs of clinical commissioning group governing bodies.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","41751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532494","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-07-07","<p>I am advised by the Medical Research Council (MRC) that the reply has now been issued to the hon Member. The MRC apologise for the delay and inconvenience caused to the hon Member and his constituent.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-07-07T15:50:34.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532494/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532494/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532494/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-07-04","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will take steps to ensure that the hon. Member for Walsall North receives a reply to his letter of 3 May 2016 to the Chief Executive of the Medical Research Council on behalf of a constituent.","false","Biography information for Mr David Winnick","Walsall North","Mr David Winnick","41725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532495","Department of Health","false","2016-07-07","<p>Decisions on maternity services at West Cumberland Hospital are matters for the local National Health Service.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-07-07T07:40:40.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532495/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532495/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/532495/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-04","West Cumberland Hospital: Maternity Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what evidence his Department is taking into account to decide whether (a) consultant-led and (b) midwife-led maternity services should be withdrawn at West Cumberland Hospital.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","41689"
